> Good news, friends: The path to sweet-and-savory dinner bliss is only 20 minutes away! In this recipe, ground beef and green beans are coated in a sumptuous sweet chili sauce, then topped with fresh cilantro and crispy fried onions. Everything comes together over a bed of fluffy rice. The results? A symphony of flavors and textures so delicious, you might just lick the plate.

In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}, @water{1 1/4%cups} (2 1/4 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, wash and dry produce. Trim @Green Beans{6%ounce} if necessary; cut crosswise into 2-inch-long pieces. Quarter @Lime{1}. Pick @Cilantro{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; roughly chop leaves.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @Ground Beef{10%ounce}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Using a #spatula{}, press into an even layer. Cook, undisturbed, until browned on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Break up meat into pieces and continue cooking until beef is cooked through, ~{2-4%minutes} more. TIP: If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

While beef cooks, in a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}, add green beans and a splash of water; cover with #plastic wrap{}. Microwave until tender, ~{1-2%minutes}. TIP: No microwave? No problem! Steam beans in a #small pot{} with a splash of water until just tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Carefully drain any excess water.

To pan with beef, stir in cooked green beans, @Sweet Thai Chili Sauce{1%ounce}, @Sweet Soy Glaze{2 1/2%tablespoon} (be sure to measure), @Sugar{1/2%teaspoon}, and @Butter{1%tablespoon}. (For 4 servings, use 5 TBSP sweet soy glaze, 1 tsp sugar, and 2 TBSP butter.) Cook, stirring, until beef mixture is thoroughly coated, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Remove from heat and stir in a squeeze of lime juice to taste.

Fluff rice with a fork; stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between bowls and top with beef mixture. Sprinkle with @Crispy Fried Onions{1} and chopped cilantro. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.